title: [Gyldemar Forest, The Barrens]
description: A nearly flat expanse of rock spreads to the east.  A bowl in the rock has collected a considerable amount of ash.  The remains of a tree trunk lie across the depression.  To the north, a wide arch opens up into a large structure.

Bathed in moonlight, a nearly flat expanse of rock spreads to the east.  A darkened bowl in the rock has collected a considerable amount of ash.  The remains of a tree trunk lie across the depression.  To the north, a wide arch opens up into a large structure.
